WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
<i>[This program is suitable
for viewers ages 15 and up.]</i>

2
00:00:10.106 --> 00:00:15.106
<i>[Call Me Mother / Mother]</i>
Subtitles by DramaFever

3
00:00:44.334 --> 00:00:45.425
Um...

4
00:00:46.014 --> 00:00:48.287
is this your daughter's bag?

5
00:00:50.219 --> 00:00:53.796
Is she Kim Hye Na from Class 1-3?

6
00:00:59.582 --> 00:01:00.582
<i>[Cafe Latte]</i>

7
00:01:23.079 --> 00:01:27.930
<i>[One month before Hye Na's disappearance]</i>

8
00:02:39.702 --> 00:02:42.966
<i>[The lab will close as of January 2018,
so please take note of the following...]</i>

9
00:02:55.345 --> 00:02:57.538
How can you manage to be
looking at this right now?

10
00:02:58.482 --> 00:03:00.531
This is the critical time

11
00:03:00.531 --> 00:03:03.363
in which all of the data from
the past year can be collected.

12
00:03:04.377 --> 00:03:07.181
Everyone else is packing their things.

13
00:03:09.333 --> 00:03:10.631
When do we have until?

14
00:03:10.631 --> 00:03:12.177
The end of this month, at most.

15
00:03:12.177 --> 00:03:14.163
I'm planning to wrap things up here
by the time the kids have vacation

16
00:03:14.163 --> 00:03:16.827
and move over to
the Pacific Seasonal Migration Project.

17
00:03:23.524 --> 00:03:25.010
Have you seen this?

18
00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:27.678
A GPS tracker?

19
00:03:27.678 --> 00:03:29.796
It sends the GPS coordinates
once every four hours

20
00:03:29.796 --> 00:03:31.220
and you can check it on an app.

21
00:03:31.220 --> 00:03:33.416
And it's accurate within
a 40 meter radius.

22
00:03:35.577 --> 00:03:37.159
That's crazy.

23
00:03:37.636 --> 00:03:40.312
By the way,
what are you going to do?

24
00:03:41.251 --> 00:03:44.595
I recovered 9 of the 120 rings.

25
00:03:44.595 --> 00:03:46.322
I'm planning to pack my things
when I collect 20.

26
00:03:46.322 --> 00:03:49.009
How will you manage
when we stop getting paid?

27
00:03:49.009 --> 00:03:52.058
I'll have to do anything I can
by using what I've studied.

28
00:03:54.449 --> 00:04:01.533
<i>[How do birds fly?]</i>

29
00:04:15.767 --> 00:04:18.002
How do birds fly?

30
00:04:18.805 --> 00:04:21.565
I'm going to draw
the shape of a bird's wing.

31
00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:27.308
If you were to cut a bird's wing

32
00:04:27.308 --> 00:04:31.820
the cross-section
would look like this.

33
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:33.589
Teacher!

34
00:04:33.589 --> 00:04:35.791
What's a cross-section?

35
00:04:35.791 --> 00:04:39.676
- Cross-section?
- What's a cross-section?

36
00:04:41.810 --> 00:04:43.545
A cross-section is...

37
00:04:57.122 --> 00:05:00.462
I thought you were going to use me
as only a science teacher.

38
00:05:00.462 --> 00:05:02.353
Yes, that was originally our plan.

39
00:05:02.353 --> 00:05:07.253
But the teacher of Class 3 said
that she's quitting immediately.

40
00:05:07.253 --> 00:05:12.450
She got pregnant with twins,
and I think her babies will be born soon.

41
00:05:12.450 --> 00:05:14.082
And the kids will have
their vacation soon

42
00:05:14.082 --> 00:05:16.315
so it'll be hard to hire
a new teacher.

43
00:05:16.315 --> 00:05:19.933
So please be that class's homeroom
teacher for just three weeks, Ms. Kang.

44
00:05:19.933 --> 00:05:23.134
And please help her out
a little, Ms. Song.

45
00:05:23.134 --> 00:05:25.120
Don't worry about planning lessons.

46
00:05:25.120 --> 00:05:26.175
I've written all of them

47
00:05:26.175 --> 00:05:29.676
so all you need to do is go to
the classroom and follow them.

48
00:05:35.421 --> 00:05:38.676
Oh Cheol died yesterday morning.

49
00:05:39.901 --> 00:05:41.498
Who died?

50
00:05:41.959 --> 00:05:45.560
Oh Cheol. It was a duck that
the kids in Class 3 were raising.

51
00:05:46.473 --> 00:05:48.944
I'm sure that the kids
will be quite sad.

52
00:05:48.944 --> 00:05:53.447
Ah, have the kids write a letter to
Oh Cheol during fifth period.

53
00:05:54.438 --> 00:05:57.555
<i>[Lesson Plan]</i>

54
00:05:57.555 --> 00:06:00.069
Write a letter to a dead duck?

55
00:06:00.069 --> 00:06:04.034
As you know,
children also feel pain from loss.

56
00:06:04.034 --> 00:06:08.466
So we have to give them
a chance to express that.

57
00:06:13.937 --> 00:06:18.627
<i>[A Letter to Oh Cheol in Heaven]</i>

58
00:06:37.384 --> 00:06:39.170
Hye Na.

59
00:06:40.296 --> 00:06:41.767
Are you not going to write one?

60
00:06:41.767 --> 00:06:45.079
Dead things can't read letters, Teacher.

61
00:06:45.666 --> 00:06:49.462
To be honest, there's no such
thing as Heaven, either.

62
00:06:50.914 --> 00:06:54.774
I feel so sorry for Oh Cheol!

63
00:06:55.769 --> 00:06:57.272
Teacher.

64
00:06:57.272 --> 00:07:00.033
Ducks can't read, anyway.

65
00:07:00.033 --> 00:07:01.473
- Yeah, you're right!
- Yeah, you're right!

66
00:07:01.473 --> 00:07:04.986
Hi, Duck. You can't poop anymore
since you're dead, huh?

67
00:07:09.579 --> 00:07:11.971
Be quiet, kids!

68
00:07:19.110 --> 00:07:21.728
When you're dead,
you can't breathe

69
00:07:21.728 --> 00:07:24.418
and you can't eat.

70
00:07:24.418 --> 00:07:25.736
That's right.

71
00:07:26.312 --> 00:07:27.678
And you don't poop, either.

72
00:07:28.755 --> 00:07:30.767
So I'm sure he can't
read a letter, either.

73
00:07:31.329 --> 00:07:35.240
But Oh Cheol is a duck that you guys
were raising since he was young.

74
00:07:35.771 --> 00:07:38.158
So to have a duck
like that die...

75
00:07:39.060 --> 00:07:41.372
would probably make you all sad.

76
00:07:41.372 --> 00:07:43.553
And I'm sure you miss him, too.

77
00:07:43.553 --> 00:07:45.935
Write stuff like that in your letters.

78
00:07:46.606 --> 00:07:49.291
So if you write a letter like that

79
00:07:49.291 --> 00:07:54.240
you will feel a bit less sadness
and pain than before.

80
00:07:55.651 --> 00:07:58.199
You don't have to write
a letter if you don't want to.

81
00:07:59.115 --> 00:08:02.014
Since Oh Cheol can't
read your letter anyway.

82
00:08:06.855 --> 00:08:08.339
Goodbye!

83
00:08:11.267 --> 00:08:13.353
- Ah!
- Oh, oh!

84
00:08:13.353 --> 00:08:15.300
Goodbye, Teacher!

85
00:08:15.300 --> 00:08:18.180
You're so pretty, Teacher!

86
00:08:18.180 --> 00:08:19.561
I love you!

87
00:08:21.897 --> 00:08:24.188
- We love you!
- We love you!

88
00:08:30.193 --> 00:08:31.381
What is this?

89
00:08:40.853 --> 00:08:42.959
<i>The secret behind Oh Cheol's death.</i>

90
00:08:42.959 --> 00:08:44.704
<i>Joo Hyuk Tan and
Jang Min Sung heard that</i>

91
00:08:44.704 --> 00:08:47.026
<i>ducks die if they eat chocolate
and cooking flour</i>

92
00:08:47.026 --> 00:08:51.527
<i>so they fed the duck chocolate
and flour every day.</i>

93
00:08:55.305 --> 00:08:57.761
It's only three weeks, so do your best.

94
00:08:57.761 --> 00:09:00.978
Looks like you'll end up learning
a lot about young primates.

95
00:09:01.964 --> 00:09:04.718
I applied to programs in
China, Iceland, and Canada.

96
00:09:04.718 --> 00:09:08.516
The Skomer Center in Iceland is quite
interested in researching murres.

97
00:09:08.516 --> 00:09:09.950
How many rings did you retrieve?

98
00:09:09.950 --> 00:09:11.170
12.

99
00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:13.842
So you have eight left, then.

100
00:09:16.911 --> 00:09:20.727
Leaving quickly,
and coming back quickly.

101
00:09:20.727 --> 00:09:22.397
You're just like a migratory bird.

102
00:09:22.397 --> 00:09:24.406
I'm thinking about
not coming back this time.

103
00:09:24.406 --> 00:09:25.632
Don't you have any interest

104
00:09:25.632 --> 00:09:27.794
in participating in society,
like other people?

105
00:09:28.390 --> 00:09:32.330
Don't you want to stay in one place,
find a mate, and maybe have kids?

106
00:09:32.330 --> 00:09:35.801
10 percent of all groups of animals
are loners, you know.

107
00:09:43.651 --> 00:09:45.022
What did they say?

108
00:09:45.022 --> 00:09:47.002
Look for Soo Jin.

109
00:09:47.002 --> 00:09:49.155
Is it... cancer?

110
00:09:49.155 --> 00:09:50.677
Go find Soo Jin.

111
00:09:50.677 --> 00:09:52.722
It's been over 10 years since we
were last in touch with her

112
00:09:52.722 --> 00:09:54.642
so how could I suddenly
go and find her now?

113
00:09:54.642 --> 00:09:56.763
First, tell me what they said...

114
00:09:57.834 --> 00:10:01.877
I want my daughter, Soo Jin,
to be the first person I tell.

115
00:10:05.228 --> 00:10:09.037
"The elephant and crocodile tried to
stop them, but they wouldn't listen."

116
00:10:09.037 --> 00:10:13.584
"Then, the lion said,
'Let's all share a little.'"

117
00:10:13.584 --> 00:10:16.805
"'I think the giraffe is acting that
way because it's hungry'"

118
00:10:16.805 --> 00:10:20.795
"'and I think the monkey got mad
because it was woken up from its sleep.'"

119
00:10:20.795 --> 00:10:25.641
"The elephant saw the giraffe and monkey
make amends, and said"

120
00:10:25.641 --> 00:10:28.239
"'Wow, Lion! You really are amazing!'"

121
00:10:37.390 --> 00:10:39.776
<i>[Normal Garbage]</i>

122
00:10:47.815 --> 00:10:49.377
Who did this?

123
00:10:50.791 --> 00:10:52.766
Teacher.

124
00:10:52.766 --> 00:10:57.915
I don't want to eat next to Hye Na.

125
00:10:58.709 --> 00:10:59.786
Why?

126
00:10:59.786 --> 00:11:04.097
Her nails are so dirty.

127
00:11:12.446 --> 00:11:14.836
<i>Do you know what my job is?</i>

128
00:11:15.655 --> 00:11:18.499
A... bird researcher?

129
00:11:18.499 --> 00:11:21.063
I know a ton about birds.

130
00:11:21.658 --> 00:11:24.603
But you know, the way that Oh Cheol
died this time was quite suspicious.

131
00:11:24.603 --> 00:11:26.626
Ducks really don't die
that easily, you see.

132
00:11:26.626 --> 00:11:29.546
But when I started observing Oh Cheol

133
00:11:29.546 --> 00:11:32.833
I noticed that he suddenly started eating
a lot less, and vomited strange things.

134
00:11:33.636 --> 00:11:35.425
Maybe...

135
00:11:36.283 --> 00:11:39.580
someone fed him something
that he shouldn't have been fed?

136
00:11:39.580 --> 00:11:44.440
For example, chocolate...
or cooking flour.

137
00:11:44.440 --> 00:11:46.729
It wasn't cooking flour.

138
00:11:46.729 --> 00:11:48.603
It was candy sugar.

139
00:11:48.603 --> 00:11:50.549
There is a way for me to check.

140
00:11:51.836 --> 00:11:54.746
I can go get
Oh Cheol's carcass

141
00:11:54.746 --> 00:11:57.478
and open up his stomach with a knife

142
00:11:57.478 --> 00:11:59.887
and check what's inside.

143
00:11:59.887 --> 00:12:01.504
And I can use the CCTV camera footage

144
00:12:01.504 --> 00:12:04.604
to find out who fed Oh Cheol
what kinds of things, too.

145
00:12:05.325 --> 00:12:06.459
Should I do it, or not?

146
00:12:06.459 --> 00:12:07.658
Don't!

147
00:12:07.658 --> 00:12:09.754
Don't, Ms. Kang.

148
00:12:10.355 --> 00:12:12.358
Can you promise me one thing?

149
00:12:13.359 --> 00:12:14.902
Don't ever...

150
00:12:15.722 --> 00:12:20.597
harass animals, girls, or anyone
weaker than you ever again.

151
00:12:20.597 --> 00:12:22.810
- Yes, Ms. Kang.
- Yes, Ms. Kang.

152
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:46.467
"Napoli."

153
00:12:46.934 --> 00:12:48.454
"Pizza."

154
00:12:48.454 --> 00:12:51.501
"It is..."

155
00:12:51.501 --> 00:12:53.671
"comparable to a pizza"

156
00:12:53.671 --> 00:12:56.165
"made by..."

157
00:12:56.165 --> 00:13:02.109
"a pizza-making master from Italy."

158
00:13:07.551 --> 00:13:09.819
There are two consonants
at the end of this syllable cluster.

159
00:13:09.819 --> 00:13:11.136
It's difficult, isn't it?

160
00:13:11.161 --> 00:13:14.656
There aren't a lot of kids in my class
who know how to read all the words

161
00:13:14.656 --> 00:13:17.310
with two consonants at
the end of a syllable cluster.

162
00:13:38.256 --> 00:13:40.474
Were you surprised, Ms. Kang?

163
00:13:41.214 --> 00:13:43.458
Why are you walking around alone
at this time of night?

164
00:13:43.458 --> 00:13:46.906
I've always walked around alone,
ever since I was five years old.

165
00:13:46.906 --> 00:13:47.921
What about your mom?

166
00:13:47.921 --> 00:13:49.296
She's not home yet.

167
00:13:58.847 --> 00:14:00.932
Would you like a bite?

168
00:14:01.652 --> 00:14:03.546
I don't eat red bean buns.

169
00:14:10.079 --> 00:14:11.978
It tastes good, though.

170
00:14:17.281 --> 00:14:18.719
Want me to give you a bite?

171
00:14:31.059 --> 00:14:33.695
It really does taste like an
Italian pizza-making master made it!

172
00:14:34.248 --> 00:14:36.454
You know what I'm talking about,
right? Napoli pizza!

173
00:14:39.094 --> 00:14:40.254
You smiled.

174
00:14:40.891 --> 00:14:43.313
It's the first time I've ever
seen you smile, Ms. Kang.

175
00:14:51.180 --> 00:14:52.609
What's that?

176
00:14:52.609 --> 00:14:53.964
A notebook filled with
my favorite things.

177
00:14:53.964 --> 00:14:56.363
If I write down the things
that I like, like this

178
00:14:56.363 --> 00:15:00.055
I won't forget them, and I can take
it out to read them when I need to.

179
00:15:01.474 --> 00:15:04.542
Um... kind of like a refrigerator.

180
00:15:04.542 --> 00:15:06.228
And what do you have written in there?

181
00:15:12.705 --> 00:15:15.093
A curving, sloped road.

182
00:15:16.310 --> 00:15:18.921
<i>Big bags with wheels on them.</i>

183
00:15:18.921 --> 00:15:22.030
<i>When balloons get bigger and bigger.</i>

184
00:15:22.030 --> 00:15:24.366
<i>A key, and a lock.</i>

185
00:15:26.230 --> 00:15:27.631
<i>[Cafe Latte]</i>

186
00:15:29.325 --> 00:15:31.329
Cafe lattes.

187
00:15:32.541 --> 00:15:33.642
What?

188
00:15:33.642 --> 00:15:36.321
Cafe lattes.
I really like them.

189
00:15:40.674 --> 00:15:42.973
Young children shouldn't drink coffee.

190
00:15:42.973 --> 00:15:44.141
I'm fine, though.

191
00:15:44.141 --> 00:15:46.568
If young kids drink coffee

192
00:15:46.568 --> 00:15:48.887
they won't be able to sleep well.

193
00:15:48.887 --> 00:15:50.445
And it's not good for their brains.

194
00:15:50.445 --> 00:15:51.998
You won't get taller, either.

195
00:15:51.998 --> 00:15:53.483
Really?

196
00:15:55.700 --> 00:15:58.839
What kinds of things
do you like, Ms. Kang?

197
00:16:02.862 --> 00:16:04.935
Eating a meal...

198
00:16:05.632 --> 00:16:07.910
quietly, by myself.

199
00:16:26.883 --> 00:16:28.259
Kim Hye Na.

200
00:16:28.259 --> 00:16:30.451
Listen carefully to what
I'm about to tell you.

201
00:16:31.325 --> 00:16:33.790
Cut your nails once a week.

202
00:16:33.790 --> 00:16:36.036
And wash your hair at least
once every three days.

203
00:16:36.036 --> 00:16:38.117
Be sure to wipe your mouth
after you eat anything.

204
00:16:39.603 --> 00:16:42.197
Change your socks and
underwear once a day.

205
00:16:42.765 --> 00:16:45.264
And if you don't have
a lot of clothes, alternate outfits.

206
00:16:45.264 --> 00:16:47.644
A dirty child will be attacked.

207
00:16:47.644 --> 00:16:50.221
Because it's a sign that there's
nobody taking care of them.

208
00:16:50.221 --> 00:16:53.722
So you might as well have a sign on you
that says you're easy prey.

209
00:16:54.777 --> 00:16:57.805
What do you think you need to do
if nobody is looking after you?

210
00:17:00.318 --> 00:17:02.507
You have to take care of yourself.

211
00:17:02.507 --> 00:17:04.572
Many children do this.

212
00:17:04.924 --> 00:17:07.138
So I'm sure that you will be
able to do this, too.

213
00:17:14.194 --> 00:17:19.159
Did you know how to cut your nails
when you were eight years old, too?

214
00:17:40.761 --> 00:17:42.113
You evil wench!

215
00:17:42.113 --> 00:17:43.744
You were so wicked to your mother

216
00:17:43.744 --> 00:17:45.976
so how dare you covet
someone else's child? Huh?

217
00:17:47.179 --> 00:17:52.244
You deserve to live alone forever
without ever having your own kids.

218
00:17:53.383 --> 00:17:56.411
She's my teacher, Granny.

219
00:17:56.411 --> 00:17:58.930
And I really like her.

220
00:19:07.655 --> 00:19:11.640
<i>- Hey!
- Stop it, that hurts!</i>

221
00:19:16.888 --> 00:19:18.580
Where's Hye Na?

222
00:19:18.580 --> 00:19:20.734
She's sleeping in the bathroom!

223
00:19:20.734 --> 00:19:24.410
Hey, it's not like
the bathroom is the classroom!

224
00:19:27.195 --> 00:19:29.602
<i>[Nurse's Office]</i>

225
00:19:31.267 --> 00:19:34.853
The nurse says that
she thinks she's malnourished.

226
00:19:35.790 --> 00:19:37.109
And...

227
00:19:37.109 --> 00:19:39.228
she has scars all over her body.

228
00:19:39.828 --> 00:19:43.071
I worry a lot for children who
are raised by single parents as is...

229
00:19:44.102 --> 00:19:45.726
but she's such a strange child.

230
00:19:45.726 --> 00:19:48.106
She doesn't cry
no matter what happens to her.

231
00:19:48.106 --> 00:19:51.367
Didn't you notice anything off about her?

232
00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:08.569
Hye Na.

233
00:20:11.707 --> 00:20:14.128
Did Ms. Ye Eun leave?

234
00:20:15.558 --> 00:20:16.648
Yeah.

235
00:20:22.302 --> 00:20:24.676
That teacher is weird.

236
00:20:24.676 --> 00:20:25.946
Why?

237
00:20:25.946 --> 00:20:28.507
I told her that I tripped down the stairs

238
00:20:28.507 --> 00:20:30.462
and she took a photo of me.

239
00:20:30.462 --> 00:20:32.551
Where? Which part of you
did she take a photo of...

240
00:20:33.966 --> 00:20:36.005
Do you...

241
00:20:36.005 --> 00:20:38.997
enjoy seeing other people's scars, too?

242
00:20:48.378 --> 00:20:50.826
I tripped down the stairs, too.

243
00:20:52.667 --> 00:20:54.576
Did it hurt?

244
00:20:56.690 --> 00:20:58.312
Did it hurt?

245
00:20:58.312 --> 00:21:00.292
Did you cry?

246
00:21:02.775 --> 00:21:03.965
A little.

247
00:21:06.051 --> 00:21:08.339
I didn't cry.

248
00:21:09.349 --> 00:21:13.068
At times like that, you should
think of something you like.

249
00:21:13.068 --> 00:21:16.033
Then you might stop crying
even when you're crying.

250
00:21:17.683 --> 00:21:19.679
I see.

251
00:21:19.679 --> 00:21:23.314
