not picking up her phone.

503
00:41:45.043 --> 00:41:48.185
Is it okay if I feed this
to Jjing, Ms. Kang?

504
00:41:48.185 --> 00:41:49.764
Jjing is hungry.

505
00:41:49.764 --> 00:41:51.875
Yeah, sure.

506
00:42:11.596 --> 00:42:13.933
There's some left over...

507
00:42:16.353 --> 00:42:18.139
so should I eat this?

508
00:42:46.648 --> 00:42:53.250
<i>Do, re, mi, fa, so, la, ti, do!</i>

509
00:42:56.610 --> 00:42:59.281
I'm not really good at reading books.

510
00:43:01.467 --> 00:43:02.766
Why not?

511
00:43:03.601 --> 00:43:06.100
Because I can't read quickly.

512
00:43:06.100 --> 00:43:07.435
Really?

513
00:43:08.002 --> 00:43:09.282
I had no idea.

514
00:43:15.116 --> 00:43:17.255
<i>[Yoon Bok's Restaurant]</i>

515
00:43:17.255 --> 00:43:19.612
So I practice every day.

516
00:43:37.592 --> 00:43:40.844
My mom is really good at cooking, too.

517
00:43:43.148 --> 00:43:44.270
Really?

518
00:43:45.431 --> 00:43:47.360
What's she good at making?

519
00:43:54.444 --> 00:43:56.398
Um, curry and rice?

520
00:43:58.677 --> 00:44:00.623
Omurice.

521
00:44:00.623 --> 00:44:02.130
Donkatsu.

522
00:44:02.130 --> 00:44:03.677
Sounds yummy, right?

523
00:44:03.677 --> 00:44:05.201
And...

524
00:44:05.201 --> 00:44:07.072
spicy rice cakes...

525
00:44:07.072 --> 00:44:09.177
and spicy rice cakes with ramen noodles.

526
00:44:11.672 --> 00:44:13.431
You must be so happy...

527
00:44:13.969 --> 00:44:15.614
that your mom is good at cooking, Hye Na.

528
00:44:15.614 --> 00:44:19.096
Yes! And my mom is really pretty, too!

529
00:44:19.096 --> 00:44:20.279
Really?

530
00:44:20.279 --> 00:44:22.297
She's really good at putting on makeup

531
00:44:22.297 --> 00:44:24.552
and she works at a cosmetics store.

532
00:44:24.552 --> 00:44:26.525
So she smells nice.

533
00:44:27.368 --> 00:44:28.913
But...

534
00:44:28.913 --> 00:44:31.208
why don't you ever put on
any makeup, Ms. Kang?

535
00:44:36.067 --> 00:44:39.018
My mom is really pretty, too.

536
00:44:39.627 --> 00:44:42.078
And she's really good at
putting on makeup, too.

537
00:44:42.782 --> 00:44:46.960
When I was young and watched my mom
put on makeup, I thought to myself...

538
00:44:47.634 --> 00:44:49.741
that there was no way
that I could do it.

539
00:44:50.246 --> 00:44:52.005
And that I should just
give up altogether.

540
00:44:53.119 --> 00:44:57.753
You didn't want to become
like your mom, Ms. Kang?

541
00:45:00.768 --> 00:45:01.985
Yeah.

542
00:45:02.752 --> 00:45:05.268
Did you...

543
00:45:06.469 --> 00:45:08.418
not like your mom, Ms. Kang?

544
00:45:14.183 --> 00:45:17.304
Then, who do you like, Ms. Kang?

545
00:45:21.476 --> 00:45:22.656
I like birds.

546
00:45:24.741 --> 00:45:32.185
"The birds... started..."

547
00:45:33.020 --> 00:45:37.185
"flying toward Egypt..."

548
00:45:37.210 --> 00:45:42.197
"and they are now already in Egypt."

549
00:45:44.875 --> 00:45:46.552
Migratory birds fly across oceans...

550
00:45:46.958 --> 00:45:50.076
on journeys that are sometimes
tens of thousands of kilometers long.

551
00:45:50.571 --> 00:45:52.985
And yet, they never lose their way.

552
00:45:53.596 --> 00:45:57.027
Rain or snow, day or night...

553
00:45:57.027 --> 00:45:59.020
they fly over chilly oceans...

554
00:45:59.933 --> 00:46:02.092
without any maps or landmarks
to follow as reference.

555
00:46:02.092 --> 00:46:04.355
But they always reach their
destination, no matter what.

556
00:46:04.355 --> 00:46:05.690
Wow!

557
00:46:06.114 --> 00:46:10.295
Because they have maps
and directions, all in their heads.

558
00:46:10.947 --> 00:46:15.868
What do you think it feels like
to fly such long distances?

559
00:46:17.743 --> 00:46:19.402
Want to go see them?

560
00:46:20.127 --> 00:46:21.719
The migratory birds, I mean.

561
00:46:21.719 --> 00:46:23.268
When?

562
00:46:23.755 --> 00:46:26.112
It's too cold right now.

563
00:46:26.112 --> 00:46:31.027
So if we get some sleep and
bring a blanket and some warm food...

564
00:46:34.288 --> 00:46:37.003
But then, my mom...

565
00:46:37.828 --> 00:46:40.864
My mom might worry,
don't you think?

566
00:46:50.880 --> 00:46:52.192
Yes?

567
00:46:53.371 --> 00:46:54.699
Yes.

568
00:46:55.833 --> 00:46:57.268
Yes.

569
00:46:59.485 --> 00:47:01.446
Your mom said that she's home now.

570
00:47:01.446 --> 00:47:02.590
Let's get you dressed.

571
00:47:05.782 --> 00:47:06.918
All right.

572
00:47:47.239 --> 00:47:48.763
Thank you.

573
00:47:48.763 --> 00:47:51.071
- Get home safely.
- Ms. Kang.

574
00:47:51.071 --> 00:47:53.462
I really want to go later.

575
00:47:54.183 --> 00:47:55.784
To see the migratory birds, I mean.

576
00:47:59.143 --> 00:48:00.447
Let's go.

577
00:48:23.547 --> 00:48:25.177
<i>Did it hurt?</i>

578
00:48:25.177 --> 00:48:26.648
<i>Did it hurt?</i>

579
00:48:27.752 --> 00:48:30.217
<i>Did you cry?</i>

580
00:48:34.199 --> 00:48:36.542
I've never asked you for
a favor before, right, Senior?

581
00:48:36.542 --> 00:48:37.960
Did something happen?

582
00:48:42.926 --> 00:48:48.395
<i>[Baek Island
Elementary School, Class 1-3]</i>

583
00:48:51.311 --> 00:48:56.045
I'll give you a call later, so can you
check to see if she's safe for me?

584
00:48:56.045 --> 00:48:58.034
What do I need to check on, exactly?

585
00:48:59.234 --> 00:49:02.647
If she's attending school
and is getting home safely.

586
00:49:02.647 --> 00:49:05.616
I don't know. I feel like
something will happen.

587
00:49:06.420 --> 00:49:07.987
Is she a student in your class?

588
00:49:07.987 --> 00:49:09.603
- Yes.
- So, why?

589
00:49:09.603 --> 00:49:11.013
I'm worried.

590
00:49:11.013 --> 00:49:13.837
I'm so worried that
I feel like I'll get angry!

591
00:49:20.746 --> 00:49:23.081
I saw the man who lives
with her and her mother.

592
00:49:24.543 --> 00:49:26.813
It was the first time
that I'd ever seen him, but...

593
00:49:28.214 --> 00:49:30.507
he had a look in his eyes
that I am familiar with.

594
00:49:31.688 --> 00:49:34.891
The look of a beast who
breaks women and children.

595
00:49:40.731 --> 00:49:42.372
Well, at any rate,
congratulations.

596
00:49:42.372 --> 00:49:44.856
A person needs to chase her dreams.

597
00:49:44.856 --> 00:49:47.227
I'm sure I'll find
another teacher somehow.

598
00:49:47.227 --> 00:49:48.789
Don't worry too much.

599
00:49:50.229 --> 00:49:52.188
Thank you for everything up until now.

600
00:49:52.188 --> 00:49:53.630
Sure. Go on, now.

601
00:50:02.896 --> 00:50:05.340
I knew this would happen.

602
00:50:05.340 --> 00:50:08.467
You've been given an opportunity
to pursue your passion, right?

603
00:50:09.581 --> 00:50:12.755
I'm sure things were quite tough on you
because of me, Ms. Ye Eun.

604
00:50:12.755 --> 00:50:15.443
So... you research birds?

605
00:50:15.443 --> 00:50:17.617
- Yes.
- It suits you.

606
00:50:17.617 --> 00:50:21.090
And your cold, callous image.

607
00:50:33.206 --> 00:50:35.300
Hye Na!

608
00:50:35.300 --> 00:50:37.626
Hye Na!

609
00:50:38.255 --> 00:50:40.028
Kim Hye Na!

610
00:50:53.889 --> 00:50:58.546
I thought that I would be going to see
the migratory birds with you, Ms. Kang.

611
00:51:51.698 --> 00:51:53.302
Jjing!

612
00:51:54.005 --> 00:51:55.818
Jjing!

613
00:52:00.287 --> 00:52:01.842
Mom.

614
00:52:02.543 --> 00:52:04.131
Where's Jjing?

615
00:52:04.885 --> 00:52:07.010
Jjing went to Heaven.

616
00:52:09.467 --> 00:52:11.653
That's better for her than
living locked up in there.

617
00:52:14.014 --> 00:52:15.794
But, Mom.

618
00:52:17.968 --> 00:52:20.104
Heaven...

619
00:52:20.613 --> 00:52:22.155
doesn't exist.

620
00:52:22.673 --> 00:52:24.767
I'm not the one who did it!

621
00:52:52.383 --> 00:52:55.285
<i>A curving, sloped road.</i>

622
00:52:57.697 --> 00:53:00.601
<i>Big bags with wheels on them.</i>

623
00:53:19.430 --> 00:53:21.043
Were you crying?

624
00:53:23.481 --> 00:53:24.979
You didn't cry, right?

625
00:53:27.548 --> 00:53:29.619
If you cry, you die.

626
00:53:31.026 --> 00:53:34.150
<i>The sound of Jjing
eating sunflower seeds.</i>

627
00:53:35.807 --> 00:53:38.182
If that tear falls, you're dead.

628
00:53:38.182 --> 00:53:40.320
If you make even
the smallest sound...

629
00:53:41.072 --> 00:53:43.764
you're dead. Got that?

630
00:53:43.764 --> 00:53:45.823
<i>The sound of waves crashing.</i>

631
00:54:03.111 --> 00:54:05.421
<i>The smell of the wind before it rains.</i>

632
00:54:07.979 --> 00:54:10.928
What did I tell you last time
about what I do to noisy kids?

633
00:54:11.744 --> 00:54:14.227
<i>When my eyes meet a cat's gaze.</i>

634
00:54:21.856 --> 00:54:24.207
But, Uncle.

635
00:54:25.092 --> 00:54:27.963
We live on the first floor.

636
00:54:28.586 --> 00:54:31.236
Falling from the first floor...

637
00:54:31.901 --> 00:54:34.253
won't kill me.

638
00:54:37.213 --> 00:54:40.215
<i>When balloons get bigger and bigger.</i>

639
00:54:40.215 --> 00:54:42.626
Want me to tell you
what I did to Jjing?

640
00:54:44.947 --> 00:54:47.738
I pressed down on her
really hard, like this.

641
00:54:47.738 --> 00:54:49.354
Really, really hard.

642
00:54:50.188 --> 00:54:52.519
<i>The road that leads to the ocean.</i>

643
00:54:52.519 --> 00:54:54.421
And then, do you know
what happened to her?

644
00:54:55.785 --> 00:54:59.874
Her eyes swelled up
like a shrimp's eyes...

645
00:55:00.923 --> 00:55:03.796
and they popped right out of her head.

646
00:55:03.796 --> 00:55:05.807
There was this liquid,
the color of blood.

647
00:55:06.746 --> 00:55:09.919
And there was also this sticky thing
mixed in there, like saliva.

648
00:55:09.919 --> 00:55:11.459
All right?

649
00:55:12.073 --> 00:55:13.610
<i>The sun reflecting on the ocean.</i>

650
00:55:13.610 --> 00:55:14.713
All right?

651
00:55:23.800 --> 00:55:27.410
You're disgusting, all right?

652
00:55:29.369 --> 00:55:31.555
You're disgusting.

653
00:55:59.657 --> 00:56:01.302
Mom!

654
00:56:04.242 --> 00:56:05.568
<i>Mom.</i>

655
00:56:05.568 --> 00:56:08.164
<i>When my mom hugs me tight.</i>

656
00:56:08.164 --> 00:56:09.813
How disgusting!

657
00:56:16.200 --> 00:56:18.117
How disgusting!

658
00:56:23.142 --> 00:56:24.586
<i>[Cafe Latte]</i>

659
00:56:24.586 --> 00:56:26.336
<i>Cafe Latte.</i>

660
00:56:28.039 --> 00:56:30.226
What time is the movie?

661
00:56:30.226 --> 00:56:32.611
I want to have a nice,
sweet cup of coffee.

662
00:56:32.611 --> 00:56:34.988
I need to get myself together, too.

663
00:56:43.528 --> 00:56:45.457
<i>Cafe latte.</i>

664
00:56:54.124 --> 00:56:58.168
<i>The first day that
Ms. Kang Soo Jin smiled.</i>

665
00:58:21.150 --> 00:58:23.247
I'm sorry.

666
00:58:39.802 --> 00:58:41.650
I'm sorry.

667
00:58:58.588 --> 00:59:01.601
Would you like some water, Hye Na?

668
00:59:08.240 --> 00:59:10.561
Is there anything you want to eat?

669
00:59:14.787 --> 00:59:16.499
Would you like...

670
00:59:17.081 --> 00:59:18.467
a cafe latte?

671
00:59:27.180 --> 00:59:29.342
I want to go see...

672
00:59:31.622 --> 00:59:35.003
the migratory birds, Ms. Kang.

673
00:59:57.472 --> 01:00:00.711
I'll tell you a secret.

674
01:00:06.403 --> 01:00:08.789
His name was...

675
01:00:09.428 --> 01:00:11.581
Lee Hwan.

676
01:00:13.271 --> 01:00:17.168
When Uncle was living with him and Mom...

677
01:00:18.448 --> 01:00:21.927
he was being too noisy...

678
01:00:22.412 --> 01:00:25.356
so Uncle threw him off the balcony.

679
01:00:27.314 --> 01:00:30.479
But that apartment
was on the fourth floor.

680
01:00:35.731 --> 01:00:37.731
You don't have to tell me.

681
01:00:38.434 --> 01:00:40.499
Don't tell me if it's scary
for you to remember.

682
01:00:44.197 --> 01:00:48.108
At the time, he was five years old...

683
01:00:49.336 --> 01:00:53.425
and died, so he can't become
an elementary schooler anymore.

684
01:00:54.246 --> 01:00:58.327
He attended Long Legs Kindergarten,
and was in the Ongdalsaem Class...

685
01:00:59.197 --> 01:01:01.825
so I wrote his name
in my notebook.

686
01:01:03.265 --> 01:01:09.769
Even if all of his classmates
and teachers forget his name...

687
01:01:10.213 --> 01:01:12.729
I will never forget it.

688
01:01:13.778 --> 01:01:18.470
Because the only person
who knows how he really died...

689
01:01:19.798 --> 01:01:22.331
is me.

690
01:01:23.952 --> 01:01:27.151
Uncle told me that he'd kill me...

691
01:01:27.831 --> 01:01:30.613
if I told someone else.

692
01:02:24.653 --> 01:02:27.923
<i>Hey, you guys!
Where are you all going?</i>

693
01:02:27.923 --> 01:02:30.798
<i>Can't you take me with you?</i>

694
01:02:30.798 --> 01:02:33.463
<i>Take me away with you!</i>

695
01:02:34.389 --> 01:02:36.075
<i>Far away!</i>

696
01:02:36.075 --> 01:02:38.383
<i>Far, far away!</i>

697
01:02:40.146 --> 01:02:42.146
<i>To Heaven!</i>

698
01:03:15.771 --> 01:03:17.140
Hye Na.

699
01:03:17.704 --> 01:03:19.206
Listen to me carefully.

700
01:03:20.655 --> 01:03:22.816
I will take you away.

701
01:03:23.380 --> 01:03:24.977
To a place several
thousand kilometers away

702
01:03:24.977 --> 01:03:26.233
where nobody will find you.

703
01:03:26.921 --> 01:03:31.572
Won't you go to jail
if you do that, Ms. Kang?

704
01:03:33.755 --> 01:03:35.356
I could.

705
01:03:35.356 --> 01:03:37.543
No, Ms. Kang!

706
01:03:39.778 --> 01:03:41.553
You don't have to leave with me.

707
01:03:42.081 --> 01:03:44.438
If you leave, you'll never
be able to come back.

708
01:03:45.026 --> 01:03:47.227
And you'll never be able
to see your mom again, either.

709
01:03:48.803 --> 01:03:51.258
But if you go back home...

710
01:03:51.918 --> 01:03:55.816
you may end up like Lee Hwan
from Ongdalsaem Class one day, too.

711
01:03:57.032 --> 01:04:02.057
Why is it that a child
can't survive without a mother?

712
01:04:02.057 --> 01:04:03.327
They can.

713
01:04:04.342 --> 01:04:06.403
And I'll help you so that you can.

714
01:04:06.403 --> 01:04:09.845
My mom threw me away
in the trash bin!

715
01:04:18.861 --> 01:04:20.650
And now...

716
01:04:21.380 --> 01:04:23.577
you will be the one
throwing your mom away.

717
01:04:29.374 --> 01:04:30.805
Will you be able to do it?

718
01:04:55.934 --> 01:05:02.508
<i>[Call Me Mother]</i>

719
01:05:02.508 --> 01:05:09.400
Subtitles by DramaFever

720
01:05:14.367 --> 01:05:17.568
<i>Let's walk on bravely,
as if we're completely fine.</i>

721
01:05:17.568 --> 01:05:20.238
<i>I'm not scared, Mom.</i>

722
01:05:20.238 --> 01:05:22.032
<i>I feel like my head will explode</i>

723
01:05:22.032 --> 01:05:23.936
<i>because I feel like
she died because of me!</i>

724
01:05:23.936 --> 01:05:25.823
<i>This wasn't an accident.
It was murder.</i>

725
01:05:25.823 --> 01:05:28.613
<i>You would've left already
if it hadn't been for me.</i>

726
01:05:28.613 --> 01:05:29.709
<i>Hye Na!</i>

727
01:05:29.709 --> 01:05:31.838
<i>Hye Na's face... is on television?</i>

728
01:05:31.838 --> 01:05:34.086
<i>- Her mother must consent...
- No.</i>

729
01:05:34.086 --> 01:05:36.970
<i>- I can't live like that.
- The child may have died already!</i>

730
01:05:36.970 --> 01:05:38.419
<i>What if she's not dead?</i>

731
01:05:38.419 --> 01:05:39.669
<i>I'm sure it'll be fine.</i>

732
01:05:39.669 --> 01:05:42.233
<i>- Quite a lot.
- We'll take it slow.</i>

733
01:05:42.233 --> 01:05:44.456
<i>Because I'll find a way,
no matter what.</i>

